The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Loose Change
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           LOOSE CHANGE
                              
	 Tata AIG Life has launched a unit-linked InvestAssure Health plan. The minimum issue age is 18 years (5 years for the child) and maximum issue age is 55 years (17 years for the child) with a maximum maturity age of 65 years. The minimum premium is Rs 18,000 annually. The fund offers a daily hospital benefit limit of Rs 500-3,000 (in multiples of Rs 500) per day and double benefit if hospitalisation occurs in the ICU. The surgical benefit is equivalent to 20 times the daily hospitalisation benefit. One can choose the policy term from 10 years to 40 years, depending on ones needs                            
	 Private sector Kotak Mahindra Bank has announced an upward revision of interest rates on its term deposit in the general category. Customers will now be able to earn a retail term deposit rate 10.60 percent per annum for the 390-day period. The FCNR and NRE interest rates have also been increased.                             
	 Tata AIG Life Insurance Company has introduced Tata AIG Life Easy Retire plan. Easy Retire is an immediate annuity plan with of purchase price which can be bought through a single premium payment. The plan provides for annuity payments which are paid throughout the life time of an annuitant.                                                                                                                                   
